Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.49,0:00:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.41,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.28,0:02:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,June 5th, 1942.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.79,0:02:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Battle of Midway, \Nthe Japanese side suffered a devastating defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese losses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,were the four aircraft carriers - Kaga, Akagi, \NSoryu, and Hiryu, as well as one heavy cruiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.77,0:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently, 322 aircraft, \Nas well as 3,500 personnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the US losses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.69,0:02:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were 150 aircraft and 300 personnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.61,0:02:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's not forget -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.99,0:02:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,one essential aircraft carrier, Yorktown \Nalso took a serious beating. {serious damage; drubbing}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.47,0:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorktown absorbed two consecutive Japanese attacks, \Nwhich wrecked her engine and caused a serious list to port.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.09,0:03:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Commanded by Captain Tanabe, submarine I-168 \Nhad to put Yorktown out of her misery. {/finish off}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For five hours after receiving the order,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.82,0:03:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I-168 continued to diligently scout the area {lit: ran earnestly }
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.77,0:03:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,150 nautical miles northeast of Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:13.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fade(400,500)\b1\fs60\c&HEBEEF4&\bord0\1a&H0B&\pos(243,592)}Midway Atoll
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However, stranded in this vast ocean, \Nwill they really cross ways with their enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ships at the time were not yet equipped with radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only things they could rely on \Nwere nautical charts, binoculars, and faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:33.81,Sign,,0,0,200,,{\bord0\blur1\b1\c&HF6F0EA&}Episode 12 \N{\fs160}Submarine I-168
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One black dot! Looks like a carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.03,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Carrier-like vessel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.08,0:03:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, the reconnaissance plane report \Nalso confirms this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.81,0:03:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt both engines. Prepare to dive! {lit: stop both sides of a ship; not sure why they need to stop for diving}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.81,0:03:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt both engines. Prepare to dive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Halt both engines. Prepare to dive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency dive. {/hurry up to}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency dive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea is perfectly calm. {/There are no waves at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. The periscope is at risk of getting spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we're lucky that we found the enemy \Nto the east of us. {lit is "I'm glad the enemy is in the direction that'll only get brighter" - assuming he means east because "I-168′s lookouts sighted Yorktown at a distance of 12 nautical miles (22 km; 14 mi) at 04:10 on 6 June 1942." so the sun was only rising and it makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.81,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The heavens are on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the reason, Chief Navigator. \NIt's thanks to your calculation being correct. {chief navigator; navigating officer; navigator; sailing master}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.61,0:04:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Time until contact? {lit: what is the gap/time between us and enemy - not measuring in kilometers, but in hours}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. We'll catch up with them in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Examine the torpedoes once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.41,0:04:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the torpedoes used in the Japanese Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.75,0:05:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,were running on compressed oxygen. {/used ... as propellant}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.88,0:05:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Max speed is 40 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Effective range is 4000 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.22,0:05:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Payload, or in other words, \Nthe amount of explosive gunpowder it contains, is 500 kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Such torpedoes boast an impressive record \Nof being the most accurate in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.44,0:05:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, the submarine itself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.73,0:05:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,also features a number of world-class characteristics, \Nstarting with a high surface speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Alongside the German U-boats, its excellent performance \Ninspired horror in all the other countries. {/... were trembling in fear}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.02,0:05:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, the weather is perfect. It makes the fierce battle \Nthat took place look like a distant dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the weather, the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, no updates since the previous report. {unsure what he means: 先ほどの報告でも }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Busted, after all? \NStill, we must make it back to Hawaii, at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't afford dawdling around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Our destroyers are at it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.05,0:06:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Back at home, our dockyards \Nare churning out carriers with all their might. {was "they are doing their best to save an aircraft carrier" but I think HA is wrong here}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.35,0:06:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But for the time being, our only remaining two carriers - \NEnterprise and Hornet must protect the Pacific at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.46,0:06:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end, I want Yorktown \Nto return to the front line as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We're lucky the sea is calm now. \NIt's our chance to withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.33,0:06:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, the wind has picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind has picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.24,0:06:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! The heavens are on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower the periscope. \NLower the transmitter. {no clue what's this haishinki, assumed 発信機 tho it's hasshinki; nothing in HA or whisper; transmitter doesn't make much sense, but I can't think of any other device on a sub that needs to be lowered... ventilation tube?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finally doing it. \NBetter err on the side of caution! {/they're strictly cautious}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.35,0:06:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is on high alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:06:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell everyone to be quiet inside the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.75,0:07:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Navigator, it doesn't quite fit your plot. {drawing a figure; drawing a diagram}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.36,0:07:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, the enemy is being swept by the wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.46,0:07:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the enemy is on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been shadowing the enemy for a while. {no clue what he means: ずいぶん敵の後ろに来てしまったな}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my fault. {/I'm sorry}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.31,0:07:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nobody's fault. {/don't apologize}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The scope of your navigational genius doesn't matter \Nin a place like this, without a single point of reference. {no clue what's tairitsubutsu} {/no way you can get close to correct result}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.13,0:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting any closer to them \Nor raising the periscope is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.28,0:08:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorktown's propellers don't turn, \Nso it’s impossible to track her sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.18,0:08:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't the enemy destroyers making enough sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to track the sound of a destroyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.44,0:08:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll pass under the destroyer. \NBut we can't track it with just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.16,0:08:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we pass under a destroyer on the other side, \Nwe'll know for sure the enemy is close enough. {actually something like "will certainly take the enemy from close distance" but idk what to make of this; the plan is to position themselves a bit ahead and to starboard from yorktown btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.13,0:08:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's way too...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bold, sir! {/reckless?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.15,0:08:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be attacking and retreating blindfolded. {lit: blind/in the dark iai; art of drawing one's sword, cutting down one's opponent and sheathing the sword afterwards​ - I really can't find an appropriate analogue in english, this plus line on 11:41; "cat-and-mouse" maybe?; for now, I'll add explanation to iainuki to my TL notes file}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.92,0:08:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do it. Depth - 45!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.25,0:11:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.18,0:11:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we good?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A two-hour dive in complete darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Depth - 18. Raise the periscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.70,0:11:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfectly on the mark. We surfaced \Nto the enemy's starboard. Thank you, Chief Navigator. {/right side }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.52,0:11:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, 500 meters is too short a distance. \NIncrease the distance to between 800 and 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.45,0:11:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The secret to a blind strike is in the distance. {https://jisho.org/word/%E9%96%93%E5%90%88%E3%81%84 - could also be "appropriate moment"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.75,0:11:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:11:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the ships stopped?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.30,0:12:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Seven destroyers at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! We've been discovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.80,0:12:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's disengage! {end; close; finish; truncation; discontinuance; closure; cancellation; breaking off; aborting}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.93,0:12:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! 12:37.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.31,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lunch time. They're having a lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.94,0:12:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All the Americans at once went on a siesta. {suspension of business; temporary closure (of a store, school, etc.); shutdown; holiday}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to launch a torpedo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All tubes ready for launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:12:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Depth - 70! Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.93,0:13:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,37 seconds, 38, 39, 40, 41, 42, 43, 44...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.96,0:13:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,30 minutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.05,0:14:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy destroyer started moving, \Nbut not towards us. {/doesn't get closer}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy destroyers right next to us. Multiple ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.41,0:14:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy vessel passing directly above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy fired two depth charges!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:14:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.82,0:15:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy depth charges - 54 explosions, 55.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.14,0:15:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Engage emergency light! {unsure what's toutsuke, prolly https://jisho.org/word/%E7%81%AF-2 }
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the torpedo rooms are flooded! {wiki says only one was flooded, but this is clearly "all of"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.44,0:15:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Stern wheelhouse is flooded!{/rear pilothouse; wheelhouse; steering house - not sure why a sub needs two of them}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.41,0:16:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Flooding in the engine room! {no clue what he says except for last word - chuusui - pouring water; flooding; douche - not in HA, neither in whisper, so we're royally screwed, put in whatever compartment of the sub you like there}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.08,0:16:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pump room is fool of seawater! {no clue what's the first word here either, sensui is "diving; submerging; going underwater" but what it may mean here? kyoukaku - no clue at all, ippai - full of, so overall: diving is full of kyokaku}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.44,0:16:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Steering inoperable! {again, no clue what's kaki, first word, could be firearms; guns but why'd he use that underwater?; "kaki won't listen"; next line may provide a little inside that it's supposed to be something related to vertical and horizontal movement; last resort for those three lines would probably be watching a Japanese documentary on submarines and praying that one of those words pops up >_>} \NBoth rudders and dive planes are busted!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.67,0:16:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Batteries are damaged! \NBatteries are damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gas is leaking! {/outbreak of gas}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.60,0:16:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,20 people in the aft, move forward! {no clue what's nigyume, believing HA tho it doesn't make sense, here's what wiki has: "all unoccupied crewmen grabbed sacks of rice from forward storage and moved them astern to trim the submarine because of the flooding forward."; lit: nijume from the back, transfer to forward}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.15,0:16:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain! The depth has passed 100 m. \NThe ship builder's limit is 75 m.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.74,0:16:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Japanese shipbuilding technology!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.64,0:16:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,20 people move from bow to stern! \NPumping station, drain one ton of water! {literally only thing I'm sure of is "mae no *** haisui" or "forward's *** drainage; draining; pumping out (water); sewerage", no clue what's his idea of making the crew run around back and forth, maybe somewhere in there, he commands them to grab rice sacks and move them to the back, since we've no idea what line actually says, might as well write that}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Put on your gas masks, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.34,0:16:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Engage the working batteries! {lit: connect usable batteries}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.66,0:17:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Head Engineer, how long will our batteries last us? {lit: how many hours remains in ...; also no clue what's the first word, not in HA iether, but ...cho has to be some military rank/position}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.49,0:17:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,About 2 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.48,0:17:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior Officer, what's our remaining air?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,40 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. If we bear with it for two more hours, the sun will set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.43,0:17:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy will also run out of depth charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.61,0:17:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, watch where you step. {lit: where you stand/at your feet}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was done in by gas {lit: was beaten/done by gas}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we had a mouse with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.00,0:17:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good omen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.66,0:17:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I-70?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.62,0:17:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The one sunk during the Hawaiian operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.09,0:17:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I-70 was departing for the battle, the mice \Nwere fleeing it in droves until none was left on board. {not sure what he means by https://jisho.org/word/%E6%B5%AE%E3%81%8B%E3%81%B3%E4%B8%8A%E3%81%8C%E3%82%8B}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I-70 didn't return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.68,0:17:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that rumor too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, our ship \Nhas not been deserted by the mice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely make it. \NWe'll return safely to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ship Surgeon, {軍医長}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,don't let this mouse die in the battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.26,0:17:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! It will be my responsibility to nurse it back to good health. {/with responsibility}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.12,0:18:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't laugh. We're tight on air. {to become muddy; to become cloudy; to become turbid; to become impure (of a liquid or gas)}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.45,0:18:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I-168 was out of power. {/lost power}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.40,0:18:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did the engine stop, \Nbut the stabilizers were also out of service. {lit: horizontal; level; even "da" also didn't word - suiheida has to be some device that levels the ballast water all throughout the sub}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.82,0:18:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, the air and seawater \Nin the ballast tanks, surrounding the submarine
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to move on their own. {/unchecked}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of that, the submarine either surfaces sharply, \Nor sinks, driven by inertia. {unsure why he says that as though it can only do one, seems to me like it'd be a combination of the two}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are enemies waiting on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.74,0:18:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And they won't survive \Nthe 4000 meter journey to the seabed either. {/can't afford}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I-168 managed to regain her balance somehow \Nand tried to bide her time. {to score (points, victory); to gain (time); to play (for time)}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.39,0:18:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The battle between gravity and buoyancy continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, this bitter experience I-186 has been through would spur the Japanese Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.60,0:18:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to remodel their submarine batteries from the ground up for to make them shock-resistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.70,0:18:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship is climbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:18:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All personnel move forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Is our crew balancing useless? {could be "tame ni"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.44,0:19:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. Please order the destruction of the secret codes.  {guess, no in HA, assuming angoubun sho / cryptogram; cipher text writing/documents - thinking he means "so that they don't fall into enemy hands"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, should we prepare the torpedoes \Nfor a suicide attack? { suicide bombing (e.g. crashing one's plane into a target); self-destruction; blowing oneself up with torpedoes - not sure what's it to do with torpedoes if they plan to ram some ship? maybe he just means "we'll die, but we'll fire some torpedoes before that"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're climbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.12,0:19:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, I'm sorry. \NWe can't stop the ascent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.00,0:19:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How long has it been \Nsince the depth charges stopped? {/how many minutes have passed since the sound of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.71,0:19:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,40 minutes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.17,0:19:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.80,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and prepare to fight back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fight with everything we got. \NLet's give it to 'em! {no clue what's this sasshiai, at all; doubt it's whisper's 差し違え}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.26,0:20:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry to your positions! {no clue, only hear "isogi de *** tsuke"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.58,0:20:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy warships. Three destroyers! \N15,000 meters. Moving away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.56,0:20:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't noticed us. But that's only because \Nthe sun sets this way. Soon, they'll spot us. {lit: enemy doesn't know, however the bright side is our way, soon we'll be noticed - he means the sun sets behind their backs, so the enemy is blinded}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.50,0:20:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up to replenish the air and fix the batteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.95,0:20:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we'll hide in the smoke! {not sure what they'll hide}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy turned back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.93,0:20:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you ever seen our captain angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.96,0:20:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Luck favors men like him. \NDon't worry! {nc what he means by "man like that is lucky", maybe he means "you're lucky not having seen it" but unlikely, maybe the previous line is wrong, but i've no clue what else it may mean}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.98,0:20:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How much air do we have in store? {/collected}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.43,0:20:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,About 70 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy approaching, 5000 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.20,0:20:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Make more smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue restoring the power! {no clue what's anything before tsuzuite, kinda hear den in the beginning, which often has to do with electricity}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.80,0:21:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The motor is operational! We can move! {/engine} {not sure what he means by "it moved"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We rushed to this battle. \NNow, it's time to cut and run! {to make good one's escape; to get away; to outrun} {no clue what he means by "battle/fight is in a hurry"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.59,0:22:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy destroyers are no longer audible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.51,0:22:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.09,0:22:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.12,0:22:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All our enlisted men got together, and well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.89,0:22:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.35,0:22:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to thank you in some way at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.90,0:22:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But it turned out nobody could find any words, \Nso we settled on bringing you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.91,0:22:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.33,0:22:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, you don't want to drink? {not sure what he means: 館長お飲みになっては?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.16,0:22:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll drink it downstairs, together with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.72,0:23:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't eaten anything \Nsince last night either, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I haven't had a single meal? {/eaten anything}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.51,0:23:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The practices are paying off. {no clue what he means by it (and judging by Chief Navigator's reaction, neither does he): https://jisho.org/word/%E4%BF%AE%E8%A1%8C is not enough/insufficient}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.45,0:23:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Navigator, isn't it beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.83,0:23:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We're taking a night trip. {walking around at night; night travel}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This submarine captain retained \Nhis mild-mannered personality
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and managed to galvanize his subordinates \Nto work together towards accomplishing their goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.08,0:23:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at times of crisis, he remained composed \Nand cool-headed. And on top of that, daring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.92,0:23:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,These smart decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and, particularly, his sound judgment in an extreme situation earned him the trust of the crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.36,0:23:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That wouldn't have been possible without his composure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.70,0:24:07.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.08,0:24:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the aftermath of the Battle of Midway, \Nthe U.S. Navy launched a full-scale counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.76,0:24:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They conquered the Japanese military bases \Nat Tulagi and Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.53,0:24:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In response, the Japanese army
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.50,0:24:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,takes advantage of the darkness \Nand raids the enemy camp by night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.29,0:24:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,However, just one decision, \Ndeeply rooted in the traditions of the Japanese Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.27,0:24:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to an unexpected mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.00,0:24:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to next week's decision: \NFirst Battle of the Solomon Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.78,0:24:38.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 13 \NFirst Battle of the Solomon Islands {第1次ソロモン海戦}
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.85,0:24:48.18,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.18,0:24:52.42,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.42,0:24:56.96,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.96,0:25:05.53,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.53,0:25:13.76,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
